content: it has been a busy week for me,
but at least I could come here.
I know recent updates have not been made yet from my part,
I will try to do them as soon as possible.
Thank you for your patience and understanding.
renju is about patience, I think....
The second thing is a good one - as most of you may have noticed, luwenzhe has developed already 4 different language versions for gameserver,
making it such a good place where different nations get together
Do I know so many languages? :)
Some day maybe will have romanian version!:)
and with the help of luwenzhe, all is possible
I admire luwenzhe's work a lot
I think this gameserver fulfills our dreams
by bringing different nations together into one place
so there are no more borders between us
the last barrier - the language - has been taken down
just borders of the renju table :)
With the help of friends coming from all countries
Now, let us get warm first before starting.
Before, slamduk, luwenzhe, coco_yuang, jamphen, Red_Zombie, leto, Ikon, shuwang, Fermat, SamSite, yyfcsd, alcore, tianxia, Intotherenju, weigui, Don, ouyang, Southerner, fallnavy, whte, moocheng.
Mr Kawamura sent me an email,
and we will discuss the date of his VIP lesson
no,because my net is too slow
but... when will be the Klimashin lesson available to download??? I'm waiting patience long time...
So, to let you know more about the great Kawamura,
I must say, he was the Renju World Champion before,
we have had 8 world championships so far
and in one of them, Mr Norihiko Kawamura won.
yes, Tallinn is my home town
and confidently won the first place.
Today we will study one of his games from that championship.
He had prepared his own favorite variant for that WC.
And it was the transition of i12-i8
this 5th move should bring black win.
But at that time, people were afraid to play it,
because they expected some surprise move by Kawamura.
He actually had a surprise move,
and maybe that can be a homework or so.
tell me the theory steps first
no idea, I don't know th theory
if dont know you can guess
and here its not so hard, yes, just one of 3
these 9 people will get cp today
and he was going to suprise with this 20
so, maybe here is a hw for you
you cant be afraid of the move that is played right after theory move
so, you will investigate to see if there is win
In our today's game, the black player is Veidemanis
What is his highest achievement in renju?
It is the country next to Estonia
im sure he is playing with friends
Still, who knows, someday those old masters will appear again/
So, the game developed here between Veidemanis and Kawamura.
Now that we know that Kawamura had his gambling plan for 5-e8,
so people wanted to see what is his plan after 5-f9?
How will he go on as white?
Yes, this is a typical development here,
I mean the logical step for balck is j9
in the end, I will add my opinion too
so please you all speak now
maybe he tries to keep black attack area as small as possible....
just by filling, keep black inside
black can not take H7 now,
so try to keep b inside first
those who do not speak up dont need to come here at all,
because to download the replay file is exactly same for them
as if they are in the room
black doesnt have good use of the 3x3
after j8, point h6 can be good for white
here is your chance to speak up
I must tell you, those who speaked now,
Now, I will say my view too
I think white decided that the traditional defence (stop 3x3) was not needed here,
because these two threes were not threatning to develop anywhere.
the j8 stone keeps white control over right win
if black will play too low
and now white's plan is clear
you can see why he made j8.
after which black could continue positional style,
and only gave blacks one area, lower, for attacks
and actually even that is insufficient for black,
and Kawamura had it all counted.
Can black keep up the activity?
it is the question we must ask ourselves
and white is about to enjoy the outcome
But can black play any better 13 here?
slamduk, please read above, if you missed our talk
is black in danger or safe?
So hard to find any competitive 13 here...
so h9 the only move here
we realize how great the 10 and 12 are
does anyone want to be white?
and the baby needs some food
almost a win, too bad black has counter VCF
does it help if white takes h9?
sooo, is my baby srtong enough???
moocheng, do you want to change 16 or 14?
I can find great moves, but have no power to finish them well
you can make babies but you cannot feed them? :)
still bothered by the counter VCF
always, black will play the most useful 19
so we try this choice first
here maybe black gets control sooner
So, this 13 was maybe possible defense.
so many 14th moves yet to be studied
no fingers warming? just for relax...
de you want to warming your finger? I have a good place for that ;-)
Let us now go back to that game
and see how Veidemanis played here.
Maybe because he was under the pressure of great moves 10 and 12.
But then, white already balanced the game.
White defended all in simple way,
but seems black not in danger yet
Veidemanis had realized that there is no hope,
so he is now playing with the tactics of filling up the space if possible.
But Kawamura doesnt let it happen easily, he defends with the move that is also useful for white self,
Does black have any power left?
such situation is considered as a big trouble for black

Then, we will end the lesson here. I will announce the credits now, however the credits are valid to those who were active in class, so later I will remove idle names from forum and quickmessages reports for todays cp.
Thank you all for coming! See you next week!
